text: The one-spot moray (Gymnothorax monostigma) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax monostigma at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Charles Tate Regan in 1909.Common names for Gymnothorax monostigma at www.fishbase.org. ==References== monostigma Category:Fish described in 1909
